ic repeated failure descriptions | ✅ |\n| AC6: New BATS tests cover all new behaviors | ✅ |\n\n**Minor scope addition (not in ACs):** A `comment_issue` call was added to the quality loop convergence path, mirroring the existing call already in the test loop. Normalizes behavior between loops — low risk, flagged for awareness.\n\n---\n\n## Part 2 — Code Quality\n\n### ✅ Strengths\n- Surgical changes: 78 additions / 10 deletions in the orchestrator; one commit per behavior\n- `_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS` and `_TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES` are reset in all three `run_stage` exit paths (schema-not-found, no-structured-output, success) — correctly scoping \"consecutive\"\n- `(( _CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS++ )) || true` correctly handles `set -e` when incrementing from 0\n- Two-step jq split for `repeat_issues` correctly handles multi-line descriptions that would be silently truncated by a single `read -r`\n- 265 lines of new BATS tests; counter-checking tests correctly call `run_stage` directly (not via bats `run`) so global variable mutations are visible\n\n### Issues","issues":[{"severity":"major","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":1229,"description":"jq `floor` builtin requires jq ≥ 1.6 — this is the first and only use of `floor` in the entire file. If CI/deployment has jq 1.5, the `2>/dev/null || echo 0` fallback silently returns 0, permanently disabling quality loop convergence detection. Recommend either validating CI has jq ≥ 1.6, or replacing with plain integer division `(length * 100 / $current_count)` which is mathematically equivalent for positive integers (jq integer division already truncates toward zero)."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":1062,"description":"Diagnostic logs use `log` (INFO level) immediately before a `log_error` in a failure path. These should be `log_warn` to surface at the same priority as other diagnostic warnings and make them easier to grep in post-mortem analysis."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":1060,"description":"`wc -c` produces leading whitespace on macOS (e.g., `\"      42\"`), making the byte count log cosmetically inconsistent. Consider `${#output}` or piping through `tr -d '[:space:]'`."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-test/test-quality-loop.bats","line":255,"description":"The replacement assertion `[[ \"$func_def\" == *'comment_issue'*'Convergence Failure'* ]]` is weaker than the original negation test — it only verifies textual ordering in the function body, not co-location in the convergence block. A future unrelated `comment_issue` call added before the convergence block would silently satisfy this test."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"c11e5b51-24fb-42c6-9021-bb833ec6cf77"}
